## Research Summary — `synthetic?: boolean` on `TextPartInput` in `@opencode-ai/sdk`

| Question | Answer |
|----------|--------|
| **SDK Version** | `@opencode-ai/sdk ^1.15.5` (both v1 and v2 paths) |
| **Type Definition** | `TextPartInput` has `synthetic?: boolean` in BOTH v1 and v2 types |
| **Runtime Behavior** | YES — the OpenCode runtime separates `synthetic: true` parts from user text internally |
| **Alternative** | Leaving `synthetic` undefined/defaults to `false` — part treated as user input |
| **Confidence** | **HIGH** — verified via node_modules + deepwiki upstream source |

### Source Citations

| Evidence | Source | Confidence |
|----------|--------|------------|
| `node_modules/@opencode-ai/sdk/dist/gen/types.gen.d.ts:1231-1238` — v1 `TextPartInput` type | local | **HIGH** |
| `node_modules/@opencode-ai/sdk/dist/v2/gen/types.gen.d.ts:1336-1344` — v2 `TextPartInput` type | local | **HIGH** |
| DeepWiki: `anomalyco/opencode` — prompt.ts line-by-line analysis | upstream | **HIGH** |
| `SessionEventNextSynthetic` event type (line 2309-2317) confirms synthetic events exist in the SDK | local | **HIGH** |

### v1 Type (`gen/types.gen.d.ts`)
```
type TextPartInput = {
  id?: string;
  type: "text";
  text: string;
  synthetic?: boolean;        // ← EXISTS, line 1235
  ignored?: boolean;
  time?: { start: number; end?: number };
};
```

### v2 Type (`v2/gen/types.gen.d.ts`)
```
type TextPartInput = {
  id?: string;
  type: "text";
  text: string;
  synthetic?: boolean;        // ← EXISTS, line 1340
  ignored?: boolean;
  time?: { start: number; end?: number };
  metadata?: Record<string, any>;
};
```

### Runtime Behavior (from upstream `anomalyco/opencode` deepwiki)

When `session.prompt()` receives parts with `synthetic: true`:
1. The `reduce` step separates parts into `text` (user) and `synthetic` arrays
2. Non-synthetic text → published as `SessionEvent.Prompted` event
3. Synthetic text → published as `SessionEvent.Synthetic` event (`session.next.synthetic` type)
4. The runtime uses synthetic parts for system communication (file reads, MCP resources, tool inputs, compaction prompts)
5. **Both synthetic and non-synthetic text are sent to the LLM** — the separation is primarily for eventing and UI rendering

### Implications for Phase 23 (Session Tracker Hooks)

| File | Current Issue |
|------|--------------|
| `src/features/session-tracker/capture/message-capture.ts:356` | ✅ **Already correct** — filters `.filter((part) => getNestedValue(part, ["synthetic"]) !== true)` |
| `src/tools/session/execute-slash-command.ts:106-119` | ❌ **Missing `synthetic: true`** — synthetic dispatch parts lack the field |
| `src/coordination/completion/notification-handler.ts:170-199` | ❌ **Missing `synthetic: true`** — notification-to-parent parts lack the field |

Both callers that dispatch synthetic prompts are missing the `synthetic: true` flag. Without it, these messages are treated as user input and captured by `message-capture.ts` as human text — which defeats the purpose of the filter on line 356.

